  <h2><span class="hash">#</span>Frequently Asked Questions about Blinkit Onboarding</h2>
  <div class="faq">
    <details open>
      <summary>What are Blinkit onboarding services?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Blinkit onboarding services help brands and sellers get their products live on Blinkit's quick-commerce platform. IARDO's service covers seller account setup, KYC and document verification, GST and FSSAI handling, product catalog creation, listing optimization, Category Manager coordination, inventory and warehouse setup, and go-live support — managed end-to-end.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How much do Blinkit onboarding services cost in India?</summary>
      <div class="ans">IARDO's Blinkit onboarding is priced plus 18% GST. It is a one-time fee, includes lifetime registration validity, and is fully refundable if your Blinkit seller account does not go live.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How long does Blinkit onboarding take?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Typically around 60 working days from registration to going live, depending on document readiness, Category Manager approvals, and multi-state GST amendments. Having your paperwork ready upfront is the biggest factor in going live faster.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Is the Blinkit onboarding fee refundable?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Yes. IARDO's Blinkit onboarding fee is fully refundable if your seller account does not go live on Blinkit.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What documents are required for Blinkit onboarding?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Core documents are GST certificate, PAN, cancelled cheque, and business address proof. Food and grocery sellers also need an FSSAI licence, and a trademark (or brand authorisation) and digital signature are commonly required. See our full documents-required guide for details.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What is Blinkit's commission for sellers?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Blinkit commission is variable and slab-based — roughly 2% on low-priced items, rising to about 8–15% for most categories and up to ~18% for premium ones. On top, expect per-unit fulfilment fees (~₹30–50), storage, optional marketing and GST, so the effective cost of selling often reaches roughly 25–30% of selling price. See our Blinkit commission & charges guide.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do you provide Blinkit onboarding across all of India?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Yes. IARDO is based in Rohini, Delhi, and provides Blinkit onboarding services PAN India — for brands in Delhi NCR, Mumbai, Bangalore, Hyderabad, Pune, Chennai, Kolkata, Ahmedabad, Jaipur and every city where Blinkit operates.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Which product categories sell best on Blinkit?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Fast-moving categories like packaged food, beverages, snacks, personal care, household essentials and FMCG perform strongly on Blinkit, due to high repeat-purchase frequency and instant-delivery demand.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>When are seller payments released on Blinkit?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Blinkit generally releases seller payments within about 15 days of successful sales.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Who handles delivery and fulfilment on Blinkit?</summary>
      <div class="ans">You send inventory to Blinkit's main warehouse. Blinkit then handles distribution to dark stores, last-mile delivery, and customer experience. The seller's main job is keeping inventory stocked.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Can I sell on Blinkit without a company?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Yes. A proprietorship with valid GST and the required documents can sell on Blinkit — you do not need a private limited company.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do I need a trademark to sell on Blinkit?</summary>
      <div class="ans">In many cases a registered trademark (or brand authorisation letter) is needed to list as a brand and protect your listings. Requirements vary by category; IARDO advises you during onboarding.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Can IARDO onboard my brand on Zepto and Swiggy Instamart too?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Yes. Along with Blinkit, IARDO provides onboarding for Zepto, Swiggy Instamart, BigBasket, Flipkart Minutes, Amazon, Flipkart and other major platforms — a single partner for your full quick-commerce and marketplace strategy.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What makes IARDO different from other Blinkit onboarding agencies?</summary>
      <div class="ans">IARDO is an authorized Amazon Seller Acquisition Partner with a physical office in Rohini, Delhi, deep quick-commerce expertise, 2500+ brands onboarded across platforms, direct Category Manager coordination, end-to-end documentation, lifetime registration validity, and a 100% refund guarantee if your account does not go live.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Can you help if my Blinkit application was rejected earlier?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Yes. We frequently help sellers whose applications stalled or were rejected due to documentation issues, name mismatches, or missing GST amendments. We identify the gap and re-submit correctly.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do you also help with catalog and listing optimization?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Yes. Beyond registration, we create and optimize your product catalog — titles, descriptions, images and compliance — so your listings get approved and convert.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How do I get started with IARDO?</summary>
      <div class="ans">Message us on WhatsApp or call +91 93101 94865 with your brand and category. We'll confirm the documents you need and start your Blinkit onboarding right away.</div>
    </details>
